Its main usage is in macro definitions to protect against arguments
starting with a control character.

@Example
.de xxx
\)\\$1
..
.de yyy
\&\\$1
..
This is a test.\c
.xxx '
This is a test.
    @result{}This is a test.'  This is a test.
This is a test.\c
.yyy '
This is a test.
    @result{}This is a test.' This is a test.
@endExample
